    <item>
      <title>Iran is not Venezuela, despite Trump’s hopes of repeating ‘regime capture’ strategy</title>
      <link>https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/mar/06/iran-venezuela-trump-regime-capture</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Experts say US influence over South American neighbour will be hard to replicate in country with deep and long-standing antipathy to the west&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, the CIA tracks the head of an oil-rich, US-baiting nation to a heavily guarded compound at the heart of his country’s mountain-flanked capital.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then, that leader is removed from power with a deadly and irresistible show of US military force.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/mar/06/iran-venezuela-trump-regime-capture"&gt;Continue reading...&lt;/a&gt;</description>
